<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1929-09-24T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1929-09-24T00:00:00-05:00" n="224" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d224">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">861.77 Chinese Eastern/368</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Memorandum by the Assistant Secretary of State</hi>
                                (<hi rend="italic">Johnson</hi>)</head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1929-09-24">September 24, 1929</date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>Mr. Yung Kwai, Counselor and Chargé of the Chinese Legation, called to
                            see me today and referred to my conversation with him of September 17.
                            He stated that he had a reply from his Government which he had
                            translated and which he handed to me, which is attached hereto.<note n="89" xml:id="d224fn89">Not printed.</note> He said that he was
                            sorry that he could not bring a more favorable response.</p>
                        <closer><signed>N[<hi rend="smallcaps">elson</hi>] T. J[<hi rend="smallcaps">ohnson</hi>]</signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>